I"E<h1 id="aris-tutorial---notification">Aris Tutorial - Notification</h1>

<p>In Aris, you can display notifications in the console, like this:</p>

<p> 
<img src="/assets/notification-1.png" alt="" /></p>

<p> </p>

<p>In order to enable notification display you need to both enable it in Aris and in Android systme. Firstly, go ‘config’ and enable notification.</p>

<p> 
<img src="/assets/notification-2.png" alt="" /></p>

<p> </p>

<p>After you enable notification in Aris configuration, you’ll be directed to system notification settings. Now enable it for the Launcher you are using.</p>

<p> 
<img src="/assets/notification-3.png" alt="" /></p>

<p> </p>

<p>Now, go back to home screen and if you see this notification, it means notifiaction has been successfully enabled:</p>

<p> 
<img src="/assets/notification-4.png" alt="" /></p>

<p> </p>

<p>Apart from that, you can also change the styles of the notification in ‘config’. We have 3 notification styles available.</p>

<p> 
Cheers!</p>

